<subSubSection id="7E9A11AEFFF5FF92FD187DB4FB79FAF9" pageId="6" pageNumber="536" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="363F4225FFF5FF92FD187DB4FB79FAF9" blockId="6.[685,1173,193,1331]" pageId="6" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis id="04F49E37FFF5FF92FD187DB4FCD9FC74" bold="true" box="[709,820,938,959]" pageId="6" pageNumber="536">Discussion.</emphasis>
This species was described by Motschulsky (1873) as 
<taxonomicName id="F18039A6FFF5FF92FC817DDDFBF1FC12" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1873" box="[860,1052,963,985]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bruchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubiginosus">
<emphasis id="04F49E37FFF5FF92FC817DDDFBF1FC12" box="[860,1052,963,985]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="536">Bruchus rubiginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because the name was preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName id="F18039A6FFF5FF92FC7C7DC0FBAFFC3F" authorityName="Yus Ramos" authorityYear="2013" box="[929,1090,990,1012]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Serratobruchidius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="04F49E37FFF5FF92FC7C7DC0FBAFFC3F" box="[929,1090,990,1012]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="536">Serratobruchidius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="F18039A6FFF5FF92FBB67DC1FD3BFBC5" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bruchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="04F49E37FFF5FF92FBB67DC1FD3BFBC5" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="536">Bruchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<taxonomicName id="F18039A6FFF5FF92FD357DE6FBCDFBC5" authority="(Desbrochers, 1869)" baseAuthorityName="Desbrochers" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[744,1056,1016,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bruchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubiginosus">
<emphasis id="04F49E37FFF5FF92FD357DE6FCBEFBC5" box="[744,851,1016,1038]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="536">rubiginosus</emphasis>
(Desbrochers, 1869)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="52113FD4FFF5FF92FBF37DE7FB79FBC5" author="Pic, M." box="[1070,1172,1017,1038]" pageId="6" pageNumber="536" pagination="106 - 110" refId="ref7796" refString="Pic, M. 1913. Coleopteres exotiques en partie nouveaux. (Suite). L' Echange 29: 106 - 110." type="journal article" year="1913">Pic (1913)</bibRefCitation>
noted the homonym and designated the new name 
<taxonomicName id="F18039A6FFF5FF92FD707A33FB79FB88" authority="Pic. Later, Blackwelder (1946)" authorityName="Pic. Later, Blackwelder" authorityYear="1946" box="[685,1172,1069,1091]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Bruchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centralis">
<emphasis id="04F49E37FFF5FF92FD707A33FCBAFB88" box="[685,855,1069,1091]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="536">Bruchus centralis</emphasis>
Pic. Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="52113FD4FFF5FF92FC087A30FB79FB88" author="Blackwelder, R. E." box="[981,1172,1070,1091]" pageId="6" pageNumber="536" refId="ref7363" refString="Blackwelder, R. E. 1946. Checklist of the Coleopterous Insects of Mexico, Central America, the West Indies, and South America. Part 4. United States National Museum Bulletin 185." type="journal volume" year="1946">Blackwelder (1946)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
transferred it to 
<taxonomicName id="F18039A6FFF5FF92FC9F7A57FC44FB95" authorityName="Fahraeus" authorityYear="1839" box="[834,937,1097,1118]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Megacerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="04F49E37FFF5FF92FC9F7A57FC44FB95" box="[834,937,1097,1118]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="536">Megacerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because of Pic’ s (1913) poor description, Terán and Kingsolver (1977) published a redescription; however, the male 
<typeStatus id="E93BFC87FFF5FF92FBBE7A60FD38FB65" pageId="6" pageNumber="536">holotype</typeStatus>
is missing some body parts, and the female is unknown. For this reason, I provide a new redescription herein. This species keys near to 
<taxonomicName id="F18039A6FFF5FF92FBA77AD0FD1FFB36" baseAuthorityName="Suffrian" baseAuthorityYear="1870" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Megacerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis id="04F49E37FFF5FF92FBA77AD0FD1FFB36" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="536">M. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be separated easily because the pygidium exhibits a glabrous longitudinal line connected with a glabrous transverse line to form a “T”.
</paragraph>
